    "created_at": "2012-02-06T20:46:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-06T20:46:41Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hmm.\n\nThe TaskScheduler disables the on_recv callback from clients when there are no engines, because it is certain that tasks cannot be submitted.  This means that they sit in the ØMQ queue, and do not trigger the callback that notifies the Hub, putting the request in the database.  I imagine I can adjust it in such a way that the tasks are pulled into Python, instead of left in the buffer.\n"
  },
